flowRoot.flowPara: To publish an application on the Flatpak Store, you must be that application's author, or one of their representatives. Please provide evidence of this.
What is your role in relation to Recipe?
Please provide evidence of the role stated above
Optional: public website of your application.
Optional: developer site of your application. Can be a source code repository, including third
party hosting sites, such as GitLab or GitHub.
Which of the following options best describes your role in relation to Recipe?
This can include links to source code repositories or other developer resources. You can also demonstrate ownership of relevant domain names, via link or screenshot.
Thanks for publishing an application on the Flatpak Store. You will receive an email from us once your submission has been processed.
Your application update has been successfully published on the Flatpak Store.
If the build is for an application that hasn't been published before, a next button in shown.
This step is highly tentative. The idea is to ensure that whoever publishes an application is who they say they are. There might well be better ways to do this than a questionnaire and manual check.
New applications have to be reviewed by an admin before they are published.
If the build is an update for an application that has already been published, there isn't a next button.
Updates to applications will probably be published automatically. However, we might want to perform manual checks if their sandbox permissions change.
